<paragraph id="C511BEE6054C6B2F829E80A504A9D03A" pageId="0" pageNumber="8176">
<bibRefCitation id="BDB2BE36476CBBF1CE1764576352D2A5" author="Harris, JG" journalOrPublisher="Great Basin Naturalist" pageId="0" pageNumber="8176" pagination="79 - 87" title="A vascular flora of the San Rafael Swell, Utah" volume="43" year="1983">Harris (1983)</bibRefCitation>
reported two varieties of this species from the nearby San Rafael Swell: 
<taxonomicName id="223069D8952BD457A7C913A7C8B82903" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Astragalus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" infraspecific-rank="var." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Astragalus desperatus var. desperatus" order="Fabales" pageId="0" pageNumber="8176" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="desperatus" variety="desperatus">Astragalus desperatus var. desperatus</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="D892C495A806536FBF4130251A9D6370" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Astragalus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" infraspecific-rank="var." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Astragalus desperatus var. petrophilus" order="Fabales" pageId="0" pageNumber="8176" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="desperatus" variety="petrophilus">Astragalus desperatus var. petrophilus</taxonomicName>
M.E. Jones. Both varieties are accepted in 
<bibRefCitation id="2313414505AF66C578306322EAE5FDEC" author="Welsh, SL" journalOrPublisher="Brigham Young University Press, Provo" pageId="0" pageNumber="8176" title="North American species of Astragalus Linneaus (Leguminosae): a taxonomic revision" year="2006">Welsh (2006)</bibRefCitation>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="F54D28DAED446B0FB066F016E6B70C38" author="Barneby, RC" journalOrPublisher="New York Botanical Garden, New York" pageId="0" pageNumber="8176" title="Atlas of North American Astragalus" year="1964">Barneby (1964)</bibRefCitation>
treats this species as containing var. 
<taxonomicName id="559EAC7E7D005B7B6968920A9498D601" lsidName="desperatus" pageId="0" pageNumber="8176" rank="species" species="desperatus">desperatus</taxonomicName>
and var. conspectus Barneby, the later of which is synonymous with Welsh's 
<taxonomicName id="4080C826D7792C88AED493E04E985A10" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Astragalus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Astragalus barnebyi" order="Fabales" pageId="0" pageNumber="8176" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="barnebyi">Astragalus barnebyi</taxonomicName>
S.L. Welsh &amp; N.D. Atwood (
<bibRefCitation id="B9720B75FA3EF5746BE9B4A7301E13B8" author="Welsh, SL" journalOrPublisher="Brigham Young University Press, Provo" pageId="0" pageNumber="8176" title="North American species of Astragalus Linneaus (Leguminosae): a taxonomic revision" year="2006">Welsh 2006</bibRefCitation>
). As our collection was vegetative, we were unable to identify it to variety.
</paragraph>
